author: Josh Feldman
title: Hillary Clinton Tweets She’s at Inauguration ‘To Honor Our Democracy and Its Enduring Values’
text:
Hillary Clinton Tweets She’s at Inauguration ‘To Honor Our Democracy and Its Enduring Values’ by Josh Feldman | 11:05 am, January 20th, 2017 
Hillary Clinton ‘s official Twitter account sent out a message this morning about why she’s attending the inauguration today. 
Even though a lot of Democrats are boycotting the event, Clinton––who lost to Trump at the end of a tough campaign––has shown up today for the proceedings, along with her husband Bill Clinton . 
Clinton explains here why she’s going: I'm here today to honor our democracy & its enduring values. I will never stop believing in our country & its future. #Inauguration 
— Hillary Clinton (@HillaryClinton) January 20, 2017 
[ image via Shutterstock ]
